summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed from The Home Land Company, a corporation to the City of Seattle, dated the 10th day of December, 1908, to The East one-half (1/2) of Block Twenty-nine (29), all of Blocks Fifty-two (52) and Fifty-three (53); Water Front Lots One Hundred and Twenty-three (123) to One Hundred and Forty-two (142) inclusive; Water Lots One Forty-five (145) and One Forty-six (146); Water Lots One Fifty-nine (159) and One Sixty (160); Water Lots One Eighty-five (185) to Two Hundred Three (203) inclusive; Water Lots Two Hundred and Five (205) to Three Thirty-five (335) inclusive; All in the Plat of Lakewood, a replat of Maynard's Lake Washington Addition, all in the City of Seattle.
